         <fig class="- topic/fig " xtrc="fig:1;30:15" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/keyword.dita">
            <title class="- topic/title " xtrc="title:5;31:20" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/keyword.dita"><xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:6;31:32" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/keyword.dita">keyword</xmlelement> element used to store a product name</title>
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:4;32:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/keyword.dita">In the following code sample, the <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:7;32:62" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/keyword.dita">keyword</xmlelement> element holds a
               product name.</p>
            <codeblock class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xml:space="preserve" xtrc="codeblock:1;34:24" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/keyword.dita">&lt;keyword id="acme-bird-feeder"&gt;ACME Bird Feeder&lt;/keyword&gt;</codeblock>
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:5;35:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/keyword.dita">The product name can be referenced using one of the DITA reuse mechanisms: content
               reference (conref), content key reference (conkeyref), or key reference (keyref).</p>
         </fig>
         <fig class="- topic/fig " xtrc="fig:2;38:15" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/keyword.dita">
